        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 21 at 4:39AM MDT until August 21 at 5:30AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Wibaux County in northeastern Montana...
Eastern Dawson County in northeastern Montana...
Southeastern Richland County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 530 AM MDT.

* At 437 AM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles west of Lambert to 7 miles south of
Glendive, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...A 62 mph wind gust was recorded at Glendive Airport
around 4:35 am.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Sidney, Glendive, Wibaux, Savage, West Glendive, Lambert, Skaar,
Intake, Enid, Wooley, Crane, Yates, Hodges, Forest Park, Stipek,
Midway, and Burns.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
